      <h1>How Many Grams in an Ounce? (Weight Conversion Chart)</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">The relationship between ounces and grams is one of the most commonly needed weight conversions in daily life. Whether you are following a recipe from a European cookbook, weighing precious metals, shipping a package internationally, or tracking nutrition labels, knowing that one ounce equals 28.3495 grams is essential. But there is more to the story than a single number. This guide provides a complete ounce-to-gram conversion table, explains the critical difference between troy ounces and regular (avoirdupois) ounces, covers cooking and baking applications, discusses precious metal measurements, and includes additional metric conversion tables that you will find useful across multiple contexts.</p>
    </header>

