    <h2>Quick Answer: 1 Ounce = 28.3495 Grams</h2>
    <p>One avoirdupois ounce — the standard ounce used in the United States and United Kingdom for everyday measurements — equals exactly 28.349523125 grams. For most practical purposes, rounding to 28.35 grams per ounce is perfectly accurate. This conversion applies to food, body weight, postal measurements, and any general weight measurement that uses ounces.</p>
    <p>The important exception is precious metals, which use the troy ounce. One troy ounce equals 31.1035 grams — about 10 percent heavier than a standard ounce. We will cover the troy ounce in detail later in this article.</p>

