    <h3>Gold Weight Units Around the World</h3>
    <p>While troy ounces are the international standard for gold trading, different cultures and markets use various weight units for gold:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Tola:</strong> Used in India and South Asia, 1 tola = 11.664 grams</li>
      <li><strong>Baht:</strong> Used in Thailand, 1 baht = 15.244 grams</li>
      <li><strong>Tael (Liang):</strong> Used in China and East Asia, 1 tael = 37.429 grams (varies by region)</li>
