    <h2>Quick Mental Math for Ounce-Gram Conversions</h2>
    <p>When you need to convert ounces to grams in your head without a calculator, here are some helpful mental math tricks:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Rough estimate:</strong> Multiply ounces by 28. This is accurate to within 1.2 percent and works well for quick kitchen conversions. For example, 6 oz times 28 = 168 grams (actual: 170.1 g).</li>
      <li><strong>More precise:</strong> Multiply ounces by 28, then add one-third of the ounce value. For example, 6 oz: 168 + 2 = 170 grams (almost exactly right).</li>
      <li><strong>Quarter-pound reference:</strong> Memorize that 4 oz = 113 g and 8 oz = 227 g. Use these as anchor points for nearby values.</li>
      <li><strong>Grams to ounces shortcut:</strong> Divide grams by 30 for a quick estimate. For example, 150 g divided by 30 = 5 oz (actual: 5.29 oz). This underestimates slightly but is good enough for most purposes.</li>
    </ul>

